Author: Godballz#9524
Content: Anybody use voat.com instead of reddit? Reddit has gone crazy with new rules, white lists, bans, and general censorship. The only thing we can discuss there is top 50 coins (even in r/altcoin!) and the only things that seem to be allowed through are projects the mods own. Voat seems to be open to discussion and free speech.  I did find quite a bit of racism unfortunately but I'm chalking that up to the double edge nature of free speech. At any rate, if more and more people get fed up and leave reddit for Voat (that's why they formed) then it can be a good opportunity for the smaller projects who already got there first. Just another angle to consider and considering the aim is to reach your user base, why not exhaust all avenues along the way?
